this is lengthy but worth the read: TINKER FOOD TRUCK IS AMAZING. the first time i ever tried this food truck was when they first opened. i’m a super picky eater (one of those, yes) and my brother, forced me to try bc he kept saying you’re going to love it. after my first bite of the arepa, i fell in love. i’m literally not going to lie, it may seem awfully crazy of me, but i go to this food truck at LEAST once a week, the rain doesn’t stop me, the line doesn’t stop me. as a college student, i’m always on a budget w food however their prices are very reasonable and worth every buck! i’m originally from west palm beach fl and believe me, no burger, arepas or fries can be compared. whenever my family is in town, they are always on a mission to go as well! not only is the food amazing, but the staff is always extremely sweet and welcoming. they’re always super remembering, kind and willing to make you smile. antonella is always extremely humble, and no matter the circumstances, so devoted to doing her job. tinker as well, is always kind and devoted to his job. they welcome their customers as if we’re family. you can tell that they love what they do. i’ve been to MANY food trucks in gainesville and their customer service beats all. the peach nestea and nutella tequenos are undefeated. if i could eat their food for every meal, believe me, i would. you will not regret visiting! i recommend 10000%!!

Except it took 2 hours and a half for my order to arrive (over an hour past the promised time). Needless to say, the food was cold and the drinks were warm. This place is officially my new favorite burger spot in Gainesville. Absolutely love it. The staff was super friendly, and since it was my first time here, they took plenty of time explaining to me everything on the menu. I got the traditional beef burger, all the way, with the fried cheese. Phenomenal burger. something that is strange, but I feel is a very good thing, is the fact that the burgers are not actually as big as they look like they are on their social media pages. that may actually sound like a negative, but it is actually a very good thing. One of the reasons that I have not stopped by before now, was the fact that I was always concerned that the food was going to be just too much. Don't get me wrong, you get a lot of food, but it won't make you feel uncomfortable. I highly suggest if it's your first time there, make sure you ask questions about what everything is. A definite must try.
